    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cups made of paper, often made leak-proof by a coating of plastic or wax; typically intended for one use. First documented in imperial China by 2nd century BCE.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
